MALE. Similar to female, except for having more robust legs, particularly the fore- and hind femora, the last one having stronger and more numerous spines. Male genitalia (
Fig. 7
): edge of epandrium rounded around anus (not evenly rounded anteriorly). Surstylus robust, inner surface with setulae stronger than on inner surface. Cerci fused together forming a triangle in dorsal view. Phallapodeme wide.
